12. It is recommended that the top management should initiate necessary reforms for fiscal reporting and accountability by:
a) demonstrating leadership by example;
b) training personnel to gain work competence and/or hiring additional qualified personnel and or restructuring existing personnel giving the right job for the right person;
c) enforcing due compliance with laws, rules and regulations on the rendition of financial reports.
It is further recommended that top management should direct the concerned municipal accountable officer to submit promptly the periodic financial reports together with the pertinent supporting documents to the concerned local auditor so that timely post-audit of transactions could be made and verification of the same could be facilitated. Consequently, the top management could also be informed immediately of any deficiencies/errors detected and corrections /adjustments thereof could be effect to their advantage.

16. We recommended that management should initiate measures designed to come up with a Memorandum of Agreement (MOA) with the GSIS defining therein the agreed balance of payables to GSIS, if any, and the terms and conditions in the settlement thereof. The following steps may help in facilitating reconciliation of records:
Secure detailed profile of payables per GSIS records;
Reconstruct old GSIS accounts, if necessary, and update records;
Reconstruct old personnel profile, if necessary, and update personnel profile;
Counter-check GSIS records with the reconstructed and updated accounting and personnel records of the LGU;
Negotiate with the GSIS for any differences that may be noted during counter-checking activity;
Enter into a formal agreement with the GSIS in the form of a Memorandum of Agreement (MOA); and
Appropriate fund for the settlement of any payables to the GSIS as agreed in the MOA.

