It is recommended that:
Management must conduct proper orientation of concerned personnel on accounting and reporting of LDRRMF pursuant to COA Circular 2012-002 dated September 12, 2012, COA Circular 2014-002 dated April 15, 2014 and RA 10121 (PDRRM);
Make sure that a separate Registry for Appropriations, Allotments and Obligations (RAAO) is properly maintained for LDRRMF, namely, RAAO – for QRF, RAAO – for MOOE and RAAO – for CO; 
Monthly Report on Sources and Utilization of LDRRMF is duly rendered; and
Unexpended/unobligated balance of the QRF and LDRRMF-MOOE are transferred to the Special Trust Fund under the account “Trust Liability – DRRM” (Code 438) in the Trust Funds books.
